Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.64,0:03:16.07,Default3,,0,0,0,,The trees don't cast shade anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.88,0:03:18.28,Default3,,0,0,0,,and the sky's cries have stopped
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.04,0:03:20.45,Default3,,0,0,0,,Where did they go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.15,0:03:22.55,Default3,,0,0,0,,And what about my voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.35,0:03:24.75,Default3,,0,0,0,,Drowning in cries,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.48,0:03:26.92,Default3,,0,0,0,,in some corner of summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.59,0:03:29.02,Default3,,0,0,0,,smiling...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.16,0:03:34.49,Default4,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,125)}All I want is to live in today, just like this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.63,0:03:36.60,Default4,,0,0,0,,{\fade(75,100)}If each time I find myself wanting something,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.70,0:03:38.80,Default4,,0,0,0,,{\fade(125,100)}I'll end up losing something else...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.50,0:03:43.37,Default5,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,150)\3c&HFFFFFF\4c&HFFFFF\t(0,400,\3c&HFFE562&\4c&H000000&)}I'm no longer someone who'd wish like that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.44,0:03:45.04,Default5,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,100)}So whatever I may lose in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.17,0:03:47.14,Default5,,0,0,0,,{\fade(75,75)}I vow to always look towards the future
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.51,0:03:52.04,Default5,,0,0,0,,{\fade(75,150)}If that's enough to make me forget\Nthe colors of that summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.14,0:03:53.61,Default5,,0,0,0,,{\fade(75,75)}then with these tears and the price I've had to pay,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.68,0:03:56.28,Default5,,0,0,0,,{\fade(75,0)\t(2100,2600,\3c&HFFFFFF\4c&HFFFFFF)}I hope I can once again sing with a smile...
